cast.overview: Spain, 2003. An accidental discovery leads Clarence to travel from the snowy mountains of Huesca to Equatorial Guinea, to visit the land where her father Jacobo and her uncle Kilian spent most of their youth, the island of Fernando Poo.
cast.title: Palm Trees in the Snow

also_known_as: Macarena García de la Camacha Gutiérrez-Ambrossi
details.biography: Macarena García de la Camacha Gutiérrez-Ambrossi was born in Madrid (1988). She is a spanish actress, known for Blancanieves (2012), The Ministry of Time (2015), Palm Trees in the Snow (2015), Holy Camp! (2017) and Advantages of Travelling by Train (2019).
details.name: Macarena García
